==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glass-snake
<hw>Glass"-snake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A long, footless lizard (<spn>Ophiosaurus ventralis</spn>), of the
Southern United States; -- so called from its fragility, the tail easily
breaking into small pieces. It grows to the length of three feet. The
name is applied also to similar species found in the Old
World.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glass-sponge</ent>⟦br⟧
